Mark Hill 2018 
(markhill1)

Chance Discovery - Working on some other data, YouTube data, with a custom command we just created.
I noticed that some of the titles we were retrieving from YouTube contained emoji.
I was very excited and immediately tried a few things, the doors were open....
Excitement.... oh my.

Usage:
Straight from the GUI search bar
In saved searches
Single Value Displays
Unit and Caption! As well as multiples.
Sizing is possible.
Retrieve them from a CSV Lookup.
Easy table row display, no CSS or JS to do in the background.

Limitations:
GUI weirdness when entering SPL.
Only some work, due to copy / paste issues and weirdness. (http://getemoji.com/ ones work well.)
Editing mainly has to be done in a text editor (I use KeepNote, this works well)
Use at your own risk, I have no idea if this could effect some Splunk functions.

Installation:
Install. Profit.
Guaranteed fun for all the family.


